Name: swine influenza
Definition: An influenza that results_in infection located_in respiratory tract of pigs and humans

Name: obsolete Campylobacter jejuni gastroenteritis
Definition: A primary Campylobacter infectious disease that involves inflammation of the stomach and intestines caused by Campylobacter jejuni infection

Name: obsolete Vibrio gastroenteritis
Definition: A Vibrio infectious disease that involves inflammation of the stomach and intestines caused by noncholera Vibrio species like Vibrio parahaemolyticus

Name: avian influenza
Definition: An influenza that results in infection located in respiratory tract of humans
